<TITLE>White House defends Holocaust remembrance speech for not mentioning Jews</TITLE>
<TEXT>
The speech was a departure from previous speeches given by both Trump s republican and d The White House issued a statement defending US president Donald Trump s Holocaust remembrance day speech on Friday that had no mention of Jews or anti Semitism because it was meant to include all of those who suffered A spokeswoman for the Trump administration Hope Hicks told CNN on Saturday that despite what the media reports we are an incredibly inclusive group and we took into account all of those who suffered Hicks retorted that the speech was meant to be inclusive of all those who suffered during the Holocaust including the five million non Jews who were murdered in the genocide orchestrated by Adolf Hitler Priests gypsies people with mental or physical disabilities communists trade unionists Jehovah s Witnesses anarchists Poles and other Slavic peoples and resistance fighters she noted The speech came under fire by several Jewish organization leaders who found it puzzling and troubling that it failed to explicitly mention the six million Jews who perished in a targeted genocide against them It is with a heavy heart and somber mind that we remember and honor the victims survivors and heroes of the Holocaust the presidential statement read It is impossible to fully fathom the depravity and horror inflicted on innocent people by Nazi terror Trump has been accused of flirting with alleged white supremacist and neo Nazi during his controversial presidential campaign Anti Defamation League ADL Director Jonathan Greenblatt expressed his disapproval of the speech in a series of tweets which he felt downplayed the suffering and persecution of the Jewish people in the Holocaust a common theme of nationalist movements he added according to CNN He also noted that the speech was a departure from previous speeches given by both Trump s republican and democratic predecessors 2 2 Puzzling and troubling WhiteHouse HolocaustMemorialDay stmt has no mention of Jews GOP and Dem presidents hav